    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p>Depth of Field (DOF) is a photographic technique used to convey scale (size) and areas of interest in a composition.</p><p>Clever usage can lead a viewer to certain parts of your image and increase photorealism by correctly mimicking a real-world lens.</p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><br/></p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"The Blue Umbrella\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639374/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717511&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639374/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717511&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639388\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"example_BlueUmbrella.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639374\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"0c3eb1bb-cf02-49ea-9e27-456843e3faeb\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span></span></p><p><br/></p><p>RenderMan provides controls for realistic and compelling images with depth of field. There are also options that are non-physical but great for creating art-directed imagery.</p><p><br/></p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-warning conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"f4754ccb-8c85-4bba-997c-135b18b0443e\" data-macro-name=\"warning\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\">The render cost of depth of field can be high as it generates noise that needs many more samples to converge. But the result can be impressive.</div></div><p><br/></p><p>To begin using DOF in Blender, go to the camera data properties <span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail\" height=\"25\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544639374/camera_data_properties.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717711&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=27&amp;height=25\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639374/camera_data_properties.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717711&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639397\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"camera_data_properties.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639374\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"2d50d06f-5135-4166-821f-4a06ee7b5ed9\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544639374/camera_data_properties.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717711&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=27&amp;height=25 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544639374/camera_data_properties.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717711&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=27&amp;height=25 1x\"></span> for the camera that you want to to render DOF from, and click the checkbox next to Depth of Field, as shown below.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639374/dof.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717711&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639374/dof.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717711&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639400\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"dof.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639374\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"be2fada7-dfaa-4fc2-8661-f7f5735d588c\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span></p><ul><li>F Stop: <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Like a real camera lens, this setting controls the strength of the effect. Lower values increase blur while higher values decrease blur.</span></li><li><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Ratio: Depth of field aspect.</span></li><li><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Blades: <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This determines the shape of the bokeh effect. If you choose fewer than three sides (triangle) the bokeh will be circular.</span></span></li><li><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Rotation: <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This controls the angle where sides meet for non-circular bokeh shapes (Number of Sides is greater than 2).</span></span></span></li><li><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Roundness: <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Values from 0 to 1 make the shape bow or flex outwards making it more rounded. Values from 0 to -1 bow inwards and make for sharper points.</span></span></span></span></li><li><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Density: <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This controls the brightness across the bokeh shape. 0 to 1 makes it brighter at the outer edge like a catadrioptic lens (look it up, quite interesting). 0 to -1 makes it brighter in the center and falloff towards the edges.</span></span></li></ul><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">For more information on the various aperture controls, see <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFH26/pages/19267659/Bokeh\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19267659\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Bokeh</a>.</span></p><h3 id=\"DepthofFieldinBlender-Focus\">Focus</h3><ul><li>Distance: <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">The distance to the object or location you want in-focus (sharp) measured in scene grid units. This is referred to as the </span><em>Focal Plane</em><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">.</span></li><li><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Focus Object: You can also select an object from the scene to be your distance. RfB will use this value over the value set for Distance.</span></li></ul><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"><br/></span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"><br/></span></p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" alt=\"The Good Dinosaur\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639374/example_GoodDinosaur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717511&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639374/example_GoodDinosaur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432717511&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639391\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"example_GoodDinosaur.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639374\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"895da0fe-c731-401c-a331-9245a3b35795\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"><br/></span></p>"
    }
